  "slint.help.title": "Naygo help",
  "slint.help.intro": "Naygo is a fast, Commander-style file explorer. Almost everything works from the keyboard; the panel with the accent border is the active one.",
  "slint.help.sec_panels": "Panels",
  "slint.help.panels": "＋ splits the panel; “Panel ▾” adds tree/properties/etc. Drag a panel's title bar onto another to rearrange; drag the dividers to resize (you see a ghost bar of the edge).",
  "slint.help.sec_nav": "Navigate",
  "slint.help.nav": "Double-click or Enter enters; Backspace/← goes up; Alt+←/→ back and forward; F5 refreshes; Tab switches panes. Type the first letters to jump to an item (typeahead).",
  "slint.help.sec_cols": "Columns (Excel-style)",
  "slint.help.cols": "Click a header to sort (▲/▼); right-click opens sort/filter/move/hide. Filters by name, extension (with counts), size and date. A funnel marks filtered columns.",
  "slint.help.sec_ops": "Operations",
  "slint.help.ops": "Ctrl+C/X/V copy/cut/paste; Del trash; F2 rename; Shift+F2 batch rename; F6 move to the other pane; Ctrl+Z undo. Right-click: open a terminal in the folder.",
  "slint.help.sec_layouts": "Layouts and settings",
  "slint.help.layouts": "The Layouts button applies/saves panel arrangements. Settings (draggable) cover appearance, shortcuts, paste, advanced and About. Shortcuts are edited there.",
